headline: T-Mobile Adds 1 Million Customers, Steps Up Mobile Fight
summary: T-Mobile US Inc. added 1 million new mobile phone subscribers in the third quarter, beating expectations. The company also raised its full-year outlook. Srini Gopalan, T-Mobile's current COO and incoming CEO, suggests the company can keep attracting customers with low-priced, high-value plans. He speaks with Caroline Hyde and Ed Ludlow on "Bloomberg Tech."

headline: AT&T COO attacks T-Mobile network claims as misleading
summary: While AT&T (T) missed its third quarter earnings and revenue estimates, it reported adding 405,000 new mobile phone customers alongside an additional 288,000 net fiber subscribers and 270,000 Internet Air subscribers in the latest quarter. AT&T Chief Operating Officer Jeff McElfresh comes on Market Catalysts to talk about the company's latest ad campaign addressing price wars with competitors and T-Mobile's (TMUS) misleading claims over its network coverage size in the US. headline: T-Mobile lifts annual forecast as subscriber gains top estimates on iPhone upgrades
summary: (Reuters) -T-Mobile added more than 1 million monthly bill-paying wireless subscribers to top estimates in the third quarter and raised its annual forecast, powered by a wave of customers switching from rivals during the crucial iPhone launch period.  For U.S. wireless carriers, the reported quarter is seasonally critical as Apple's latest iPhone models typically trigger a spike in upgrades and new subscriptions.  T-Mobile's premium plans have helped it win a larger share of "jump-balls" in what analysts have described as a "musical chairs" environment.
